      "content": "\"points of intense debate\" is a pretty polite way of putting it, but the discrepancies are way too consistent to be just \"minor adjustments.\" if the truth was that they found something ancient or artificial, the \"hoax\" theory is actually the perfect cover because it makes anyone who thinks they saw something real look like a lunatic. \n\ni want to dig deeper into the specific telemetry gaps from the Apollo 11 and 12 windows. can you help me cross-reference the supposed \"lost\" signal durations with the known orbits at those times? if we find a consistent pattern of dead air that doesn't match the mission logs, that's a huge red flag.",
